column1:
Even though the actual apt listed was not ready due to a renovation delay, Jia was gracious and nice enough to let us stay in her own apt, which turned out to be very large, nice and comfortable place. We felt very much at home and had a great time. My husband and I were there for the World Expo so we, unfortunately, didn't get a chance to explore the neighborhood as much as we liked, but it of what we saw, we really liked. 

My only complaint is that the apartment we stayed in was in a very residential area and the walk to the subway was a bit far. Taxis are very affordable, but sometimes difficult to find a free one. Of course this might not pertain to the actual apt Jia has listed, which, I think, is located closer to the subway. 

Overall, Jia was a great host. She was very accommodating, helpful and made us feel very welcomed. She helped us order a taxi on our last day and even introduced us to local Chinese teas and fruits as well. :) I would highly recommend her!

Jia's place is in a vibrant and (in my opinion!) the most beautiful section of Shanghai. The French Concession is known for its leafy streets lined with cafes, boutique shops, upscale spas, yoga studios, and art galleries. Shanghai__ nickname as the __aris of the East_ evidently stems from the tree-lined avenues, Tudor mansions and French-influence architecture of this district. Exploring every alley of this graceful district would likely take a long time, and the constant renewal process that occurs in Shanghai insures that the urban landscape will likely be quite different in a few years than what it offers today. In particular I liked the area just north of Huaihai Rd, as Fenyang Rd. turns into Donghu Rd. Within a 10-minute walk you have your choice of dozens of upscale delicious ethnic restaurants and it is less than a 10-minute walk to Changshu Rd. subway station. Centrally located within Puxi, the center of Shanghai, you couldn't ask for a more convenient location. One thing I really like about Jia's apartment is that music can be heard from all corners of the apartment complex. Just next door a junior high school student practiced the violin for hours upon hours a day. Across the courtyard, there was the sound of a saxophone, and around the corner someone practiced Chinese folk songs on a dizi. This really enchanted my daily life. Since the apartment is just around the corner from the Shanghai Conservatory of Music, the entire area is packed with music shops selling scores, CDs, and instruments. The apartment is not large but clean, well-appointed, and gets great light. I really enjoyed washing my laundry and hanging it out to air-dry on bamboo poles like my Chinese neighbors! Make sure you you use clips though, or your clothes will fall down to the 1st floor garden apartment! The friendly security guard had to help me retrieve my clothes. The apartment is in a very safe area and is constantly under surveillance by a security guard. Although it is always a good idea to lock your windows in any large city, it is unlikely that a thief could enter this complex unnoticed. At night, a large gate to the complex is closed to prevent traffic from entering and guests must check in with a security guard. Although Fuxing Rd. is busy and noisy, the apartment is set back from the main road so it is quiet and peaceful at night. There were a few minor maintenance issues with the apartment during the time I was there, but Jia always responded promptly. Even when she couldn't come over herself, her adorable father would eagerly come over to help! I must admit that my body didn't react well at first to Shanghai and I was sick on and off for about two months, not to mention suffering somewhat from culture shock. Jia helped me more than once with medicine and the like and provided a compassionate ear. On more than one occasion she invited me...
The host canceled my reservation the day before arrival.
Very Nice Place, Convenient and Comfortable for Staying.

Very friendly host who was helpful and really tries to make our stay and enjoyable one. Great check-in and check-out time, and FANTASTIC location near two malls and a metro station with connections to 4 lines to take you around Shanghai.

The place is very neat and close to subway station. Xuexia prepared almost everything you need to stay comfortable. But one of the bedrooms is separated from the living room by a curtain. If you or your friend need more privacy or quieter sleeping surrounding, you probably need to take some consideration.

The transportation is very convenient. It's near the exit of the subway station. All three beds are good, and the kitchen and dining room are surprisingly large. The only fly in the ointment was that the neighborhood was a little old and the elevators were slow. But overall, it's recommended.
A nice apartment but quite noisy at night.

Address is very confusing, expect to contact the host to get to the apartment. Narrow staircase walk up to the unit, big luggage may not advisable. Water heater is tricky, you may not get the hot water consistently.

Excellent location, and easy to access to nice local bars, cafes. Room is clean with chic style . It was pleasure to meet Liting and her friends. She showed me some nice local bars, and shopping district. She is a wonderful host and very easy going.

Liting is a charming girl she provides good recommendations for bars in the block and very easy to communicate with. 
The house__ location is perfect, next to Ferguson Lane, I think it__ the best place you can find in SH to spend your time. If you travel alone, I think you should try to live here. I have spent some good time, miles is cute,too
Excellent location.  Close to public transportation.   Fun neighborhood.  Liting was a gracious host.

Liting is a very nice and friendly host.
The room is bright and neat, with a comfy bed and air con, and the neighbourhood is great to have a walk or a coffee, and to dine out

Liting__ place is great! It is fully furnished and beautifully designed :) I enjoyed staying and meeting Liting & her lovely cats. Her place is located in cool neighborhood where you can see a lot of interesting cafes, bars and restaurants. I would definitely recommend her place to anyone who visit Shanghai! Thank you Liting.
Liting__ place is quite convenient in the French Concession. Easier to access. Thanks for the hospitality
Good host and convenient location! I do recommend to live in here!
At central Shanghai with convenient location.

The host is a super elegant woman, her look, her style, her music, I just love love love everything about her! And her cats are adorable too! They are really close to people, which is rare;) as for the place, it__ actually a shared room. I didn__ notice that during booking. I gotta say it__ a little disappointing since I am the kinda person who values privacy and craves for staying all alone after a tiring day. Since it__ a shared house, that means you__l stay with the host. It__ inevitable to be not that clean, which bothers me a little but I really love the scent of the place and the hospitality of the cats ;) plus, I really love the songs that the host kept playing, really groovy!

Highly recommended for location - it was conveniently located in the French concession, and there were a lot of nice streets nearby to walk. Liting was also very friendly and made us feel very welcome.

Very nice and quiet neighborhood, easy access to 24 hour convenience store and a famous Shanghainese restaurant. Across street from a live jazz place. Walking distance to Jiaotong University subway station which has a direct link to Hongqiao Airport or Railway Station. The host is a nice and pretty girl. The downside is that the place has no elevator, it__ a pain to carry the luggage all the way upstairs and downstairs. In addition, it__ quite a surprise that the lock to the bedroom is broken, therefore the cats and the host can inadvertently break into the room which is quite a disturbance for me. The tiny kitchen is always messy that can use some cleaning. It__ not that desirable for any cooking there.
Had a lot of fun playing with her cats. Very friendly and showed me around

Liting is so nice and the room is wonderful! I've been Shanghai for many times but this time I felt really comfortable and satisfied.
Few minutes for walking to the subway station and bars nearby just make this place perfect.

Only stayed here for a couple days, I felt at home~ In my travel schedule I would love to have local experiences and make some new friends, and dear liting offered very considerate help and many tips in great restaurants and amazing art exhibitions while she knew I didn__ have much travel schedule. Cute cats, stylish place, convenient transportation, comfy corner at bedroom, __idnight dinner_ etc. The soup is not only of good taste, but also love from ting. So it deserves a five star coz exceed my expectations. Many thanks to this cutie pie and hope to see you again in Shanghai or Canton.

Highly recommended!
The host is very friendly and enthusiastic. I lived here for two month during which I would always receive some dessert from the host including rice-pudding, cake, watermelon... whenever I met some issue, he would respond quickly and solve it patiently.
There is a lovely cat in the apartment that was always curious to enter my room and explore. (So cute)
As for the address, the nearby environment is quiet and peaceful. There are supermarkets nearby and the nearest shopping area is around 15 mins walk (5mins cycling). By the way, you can view the Oriental Pearl Tower at the rooftop of the apartment.

The room is about 1 km too far from the closes the metro station, but besides from that I am very happy with my stay. Jun, the host, was the best host I__ ever had, picking me up at the metro station, helping me with my big luggage, answering all of my questions, and even inviting me to have a meal with him and his wife. A wonderful experience. Would definitely stay her again despite the distance.
Great hospitality, clean room with lots of place, and a lovely family. I strongly recommend

Staying at Sean__ place is one of my best Airbnb experience, I have to say. 
Both of them two hosts are suuuuuuper nice and outgoing. Basically you could ask them for any help you need. And their interaction with kimi(the cat) is so lovely and kimi is our little baby. lol
The room is stylish and cozy. The home is tidy and warm. The cat kimi is my sweetheart. Every time I went back home and she would wait for me in the front of the gate. 
Definitely recommend!!!!

Okay let me think of something more to talk about...
The home has laundry devices and a large TV, a nice view of Shanghai skyline. I know the fact that Sean and junyi want to hear sweet words from me and they will feel extremely happy about that but I have to save my words cuz my trip still not end right now and I love them

While the host are really nice and helpful I don__ think the place is for tourist. It is very local in a old building where you will have to travel up to the sixth floor with your luggage in a stair case that__ pitch black. The pillows are too soft and bed is not that great however, one may could make it work if needed be. Please keep in mind that everyone shares one bathroom as I was confused a bit from the pictures. I decided to check out early and since we were on the 6th floor I had to take one bag down at a time, and got locked out the apartment. I missed my flight and had to wait all day to get my luggage as no one was home. I could not find the MTR station and did not feel safe in neighborhood.

This accommodation turned out to be much more than just a stylish place to stay in! Of course the design of the place caught my eyes in the first place, in real life it really looks likes a place popped out of (Hidden by Airbnb) , with great colors of green and gold. I especially like the bathtub in the bathroom. The location was awesome, it__ in a very local residential compound, but it__ actually in a quite hip area crowded with restaurants, bars, cafes and cool people. The shampoo, shower gel, and body lotion is of good quality, not something from some crappy convenient stores from across the street. It__ also equipped with speaker (Marshall!!! i always need to carry a small speaker with me when I travel, so this is insanely helpful to me!) and coffee machine (Nespresso). I lived by myself this time, but it has two bathrooms actually, both places have toilets and showers. And the sofa can also be used as a bed, and actually 4 people can live in this place. Overall, it__ been an awesome experience. Oh also, I think you can take some great photos for your friends in here too.

I had headaches choosing a good place to stay until I discovered this one in the French Concession. The location is so convenient - I literally just walked to brunch with my friends and we spent the whole afternoon wandering around small shopping stores across the streets. The interior of this suite relaxed me immediately when I walked in. I was also surprise by the high-quality amenities in the kitchen and bathrooms. The rooms were super clean, new and quite, completely different to some other old townhouse rooms I stayed in Shanghai. Highly recommend this place!
A place that__ makes you feel peace and quiet from the busy city. The color also gives people a very nice and cosy feeling.
2nd stay here. Definitely love this place!

This is a great place for anyone that wants to get a feel for one of Shanghai's coolest neighborhoods and avoid staying in a high rise hotel in the toursity part of town. Ryan's place offers amazing access to the Former French Concession's many restaurants and shops. The unit was  comfortable and spacious, and Ryan did a great job communicating with us throughout.
Comfortable and well appointed place in a really nice part of town.
Lovely place ,nice host ,cute dog near ,super nice !

We stayed here in An Fu Lu area in our time in China. Even paid a steep cancelation fee at another place to book this one and so glad we did. After visiting Xi__n and Beijing the first week of the trip, this was the third place we stayed. Hands down the best one! Very clean, you could smell it, very stylish, and just a great place. As a tourist, we didn__ know what to expect but this was awesome. Everything you could want is walkable and you feel very safe walking, even late at night. Great place, and a great host.

Located right at the heart of old French quarter.
Tastefully decorated with thoughtful touches.
Warm hospitality.
Great place that__ roomy and centrally located. Would definitely stay here again!
Location is good, lacks hot water, impossible to lock doors of bedrooms

Moyan & Dailin__ place is great! The location is absolutely central - it__ less than 5 mins (slow) walk to metro West Nanjing Road. The place is small but really clean and has everything you need. If I could give 4.5 stars, I would. This is a very well designed apartment in a fantastic location. The apartment is in a historic building across the street from three subway lines and the world__ largest Starbucks. It is perfect for a single person or a couple. Dailin and Moyan were great hosts who want you to be comfortable. I stayed more than a month, so Dailin hired cleaners each week to change the linens. I speak Chinese and was friendly with several of the neighbors, all of whom were very welcoming. The only drawbacks are that in a historic property, there can be problems with old plumbing and seasonal insects, but Dailin and Moyan are quick to help solve any problems! (Shanghai had a problem with termites this June__everal of my Chinese and foreign friends also had problems--but this wouldn__ be a problem at other times of the year. The apartment is very close to Donghua University and Metro lines 2, 3 & 4.  Xinhing Bridge Park and Hongqiao Park are close.  High quality supermarkets, Ole and City Super, are very close. The apartment has a large fridge, washing machine, heating/aircon, bathroom with a separate shower and a stove top.  The apartment was very clean.  The apartment is very girlie with pink everywhere, but I knew that from the pictures. It didn't bother me. There are only small pots for cooking so I needed to buy a wok.  The largest towel available is a hand towel.  This was frustrating but the owner did state that in the ad so I was prepared. The apartment is on the 3rd level.  The wifi downloading is fine but uploading was very slow. The apartment is very close to the Yan'An Elevated Road and I could hear the traffic.  However, when I had the air conditioner on I could not hear the traffic.

The room and the apartment building are not as new as it seem. Especially the elevator hall, it was quite dirty.
Sound proof was very bad. I was wokr up by a noise neighbour who was playing some music at 6:30am.... I had to knock on her door to stop the noise. 
The apartment was equipped with all necessary amenities, but like the room itself they were bit old.. The air-conditioner was dusty and making weird sound.. 
The last let down was the view. I chose this apartment mostly because I liked the window seat and the view (I was expecting a nice view). But it was quite a shocker when I open the curtains... It faced right to a half abandoned parking lot...

I was worried I would not be able to make it around very easily but Jennifer was able to respond quickly and send me the address so I was able to quickly copy and past the address. Even better the stay was amazing and sparkling clean! I can not wait to come back in the future.

I am highly impressed and overwhelmed by the friendliness of Helen and Zheng. They have offered me not just a room but a home for now 1 month and I will stay another one in their home. The room is very clean and offers everything and more than I could need. Helen is a great cook and they invited me to eat with them quite often. I would even say we became friends. When I arrived in China because of my businesstrip I did not know anyone except of my colleagues, so she asked me if I wanted to play ping pong with her and her friends.
Sometimes we sit together in the evening and teach each other languages (chinese, german, english) it is always funny. 
I can only recommend this air bnb room. If you want privacy you get it and if you are a open minded communicative person you can have people to talk to. I am very glad that I found this room.

After 2 months in Helen and Zheng's appartement, i can truly say that the accommodation and is absolutely beautiful and clean and the hosts are very kind.

 I had a clean room,a comfortable big bed and enough space to storage my clothes and goods.

The kitchen is well equiped so I could cook by myself or together with my hosts.

We had a close relationship during my stay. Spend the weekends together, playing ping pong and singing karaoke.

Helen cooked nearly every evening and as she and her husband are very good in cooking, I enjoyed every meal. Sometimes even finger licking.

I am very glad that I had the chance to live here, because I did not only find a room, but a home in china.

I stayed at this lovely residence from July 24th - August 1st.... Greeny was lovely with the communication about where to find the place, Wi-Fi password, hidden key etc. 
As for the place itself.... it is in an older building adjacent to the W Hotel and a fancy smancy mall and within a two - five minute walk from International Cruise Terminal Station on Line 10 (about 45 minutes from Hongqaio Airport and about the same to Pudong Airport).... The interior was very modern and it has Western Amenities such as a Western toilet (w/ washlet) and a updated shower. The room has a outrageously beautiful balcony that overlooks the Pudong Financial District in front of you while the Bund will be on the right side. Not only is it easy to access the metro to anywhere in the city there but also you can take a 15 minute walk to the Bund and sightsee or another 20 minute walk to see the SNH48 Theater. There are a couple of convenience stores within 2 minutes and the the Wi-Fi was strong as well. As of the time of this writing, they are doing construction on the room next door so you might get some clanging and banging but if you leave early and come back late, you won't notice a thing. Anyways, it was a great place to stay and I can't wait to make a return trip!

My friends and I spent 3 nights at the property and here are some honest comments from us.

Overall
-the apartment was conveniently located within 5-10min from the MTR station and it looked exactly as the pictures shown; however, it was poorly maintained and there__ definitely a lot of room for improvement regarding its cleanliness.

Cleanliness
-strong moldy scent upon our arrival, even with the air-conditioning on
-the bathroom and bean bags in the living room had visible molds on them
-one of the blankets had blood stain on it (which we later found that this had already been mentioned in another review back in Feb (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) , meaning the blanket had not been washed since then!)
-fridge was not plugged in and smelled disgusting
-walls were stained as well

Facilities
-steamer was dusty af, not sure if it had ever been used (or cleaned)
-low water pressure as expected, but the water pipe broke during our stay and the water heater got cut off, which one of my friend had to shower in freezing cold water in the middle of the night
-thin walls, we had no problem listening to the TV next door or our upstairs neighbor
-VERY STEEP STAIRS!

Host
-friendly and easy to reach through (Hidden by Airbnb) 
-responded very quickly to all our queries
-less proactive in suggesting attractions or restaurants nearby
-user manuals of the appliances were only sent as per request

Final verdict
-as an airbnb plus property, its standard is definitely not up to par
-not worth the money

The apartment of Lisa is a special place, charming and comfortable. 
 Lisa is a very careful landlady. She provided towels and  double bed sheets for every bed as well as Italian cafe and cafe-machine and some cookies as welcome.
The apartment is located in an elegant and calm area but close to shops (also international market), restaurants and bar. It is quite spacious, very well mantained and clean. The furnitures are a mixture of IKEA and traditional style and there is plenty of room for clothes, shoes etc. There is also a piano! 
The bathroom is very large with bath tube and washing machine. The shower works quite well and hot water is always available.
The kitchen is very well equipped, I prepared the food myself almost every day! 
Also the single bed room (without window) is a cosy and comfortable room. I shared the apartment with a colleague for 1 full months and we never got in trouble for lack of privacy or unbalanced confort.
Finally the entrance hall and stairs are in good state and clean, and this is not easy to find in Shanghai.

We loved it. The apartment is very clean, it has a stylish decoration with a cosy touch, it's not super big but it's good enough for 2-3 people to stay. It is well located, pretty much in the heart of the former french concession. The host is amazing (both Lisa and her uncle), really helpful and welcoming. We stayed for almost 3 months and Lisa was always replying fast and helping us with any arrangements. There are nice areas to walk around and good restaurants to visit. Lisa's place is totally recommended and we would love to stay again!

Candice is very nice and easy to communicate, promptly response.
All in all, highly recommend.
A very clean and quiet apartment in a very convenient location.  The Auchan nearby and the convenient access to Line 8 and many bus routes made getting around easy.

Very cozy place in the heart of Shanghai, perfect for solo or couple travelers. Found a bug on the left hand side of bathroom sink, and surprise, another underneath my pillow. Great experience 

Only good thing about the place is location. Very close to everything.
Fiona was quick to respond, apartment was located quite centrally within walking distance of a lot of restaurants, bars and supermarkets.

The host is extremely nice! 

The place itself is tiny though, only suitable for those light traveler who only has one mini suitcase, and not too tall!

Sleek and minimalist design, both interior and exterior, and the hotel as a whole really stood out from the other surrounding buildings. Host and staffs were friendly and will go out of their way to find the best route to your destination. Other than that, I really like that dorms are separated by gender by default because the last capsule hotel i stayed (in Malaysia) you'll have to pay an additional fee to have an all girls room. Ive been to Shanghai a few times and I'd say this would be the most valued for money location, the train station is also only a walk away and this is just three stops away from nanjing road where i did most of my shoppings. The capsules were very clean and tidy and daily essentials were provided. Overall I'd give it a 5 stars cause of the brilliant hospitality and design. Would definitely want to go back again.

The staff members at Weflow were professional and accommodating from beginning to end. They quickly responded to my queries before I arrived and kindly helped me with all my needs during my visit. The facility was kept immensely clean and I felt very safe in the hostel and in the surrounding neighborhood (make sure to wander about the neighborhood to find many gems such as large indoor markets with delicious food stands and the international tea culture square. In fact, I spent more time in that neighborhood than any other single area). It's only 3 stops from the heart of downtown and a 5 minute walk to the Metro. I will absolutely stay here if I ever come back to Shanghai.
This place is absolutely wonderful. I would stay here any time.
The place is extremely stylish and clean, just like the photos! Also located really near the metro so that makes traveling very convenient
With the price as such, one could find a hostel in a more central and culturally enriched area. The communication with staff and solutions could also have been more honest and straightforward.
Good & friendly host. Highly recommend here.
stylish place. 8min from metro. very nice host!
Kristy is a responsive host and renders her assistance during our stay. She is a very kind and sweet host.

Would definitely recommend this Airbnb! Great location, 10 minute walk from People's Square and a few minutes walk from restaurants! Kristy is also very quick and prompt with responses - there was an issue with the door and Kristy fixed it straight away!

Kristy has been an amazing host. She was extremely responsive to my needs especially when I was locked out of the flat, making sure I regained access quickly.

This opportunity to live in an original vintage style part of Shanghai but with modern amenities has been incredible. 

Be warned the stairs are a little vintage and narrow as well, pack light where possible. 
The area was safe, convenient and quiet at the same time. Neighbours were friendly and helpful. The flat has natural lighting which makes getting up more comfortable. 

Perfect for one to two person stay.
very cozy little loft. nice and clean

Kristy and her boyfriend who helped us check in after being unable to find the place despite instructions were nice.
The place however, does not look like the images, the surrounding area and staircase leading up to the apartment were dilapidated and a safety hazard. This place was not for us and I__ request surrounding area pictures, up-to-date apartment images and staircase images and proof of working safety features in the building itself not just the apartment (fire alarm, carbon monoxide detector, etc. etc.) before staying here. I understand wear and tear are inevitable, but this was not just wear and tear it was stained carpets, burned hallway walls and a very less than ideal surrounding area. This place wasn__ for us and we left as soon as we could and booked a hotel and immediately took a taxi to the downtown area.

The host was very helpful, even assisted me with (Hidden by Airbnb) /phone payment issues I was having. The bedroom (duplex part) was dark and quiet, and the bed linen were excellent (high thread count), excellent if you expect/have a jetlag.

The apartment is the top floor of an old Shanghai-style house. So yes, that means climbing some stairs. But that also gives you the Shanghai-experience. And there are no people cooking in the staircases (that does happen in some Shanghainese houses).

Location-wise the apartment is very well situated. Walking distance to People's Square, and from there you can take subways everywhere. Taxi (and Didi) drivers can also easily find the right intersection, and I've also biked to some locations and went to Suzhou river for a run.

Internet, laundry machine and TV (I connected my laptop with my own HDMI cable) also worked perfect.

The room and location are very respectable. Be ready for some local interactions and and experiences; an older couple lives on the second floor. Personally, I asked to check in at an earlier time and it seemed like the cleaning person was rushed. I had to vacuum the area myself. The host was receptacle to advice, and I hope your experience is a little better.

Everything you need and nothing you don't in a classic Shikumen building.

Really charming renovation of the apartment: makes it light and airy.  Washing machine was a plus.  Convenient to anywhere around People's Park or Nanjing Rd.

Awesome little loft located short walk from People__ Square metro station and great restaurants as well as museums. Additionally, only a couple stops away from Shanghai Railway Station so super convenient. Stairs up to apartment are a bit small and old so try not to overpack!
What you see is what you get! Nice and cozy place to stay! Clean and tidy!

Excellent location! People Square and Subway Stations are very close. You can basically walk 5-10 minutes to various Museums, Malls, Nanjing Road, Restaurants, etc. Great host. Responds quickly to your messages. The apartment is exactly what you see in the photos. A little small, but perfect for a short stay. Highly recommended!!!

The location is great.  Major attraction, such as Shanghai Museum, People's Square, Shanghai Urban Planning Museum, etc. are all in short walking distance.  The metro is also nearby that takes you to The Bund, Pudong Financial District, Yunnan Garden, Jinan Temple, etc.  Like you see in the photo, the place is simple and basic, and a perfect space for single, or couple accomodation.  It's on the top floor and the common staircase is narrow with no elavator.  During my 4 nights stay, I found it relatively quiet at night, but in the morning, it gets a bit noisy due to workers outside working on renovation next door.

The interior was cozy but the external environment of the area was not very pleasant, especially the staircase was narrow and dirty. Some renovation works were carried out at the staircase since the first day of my vacation starting at 6 am !! It was noisy and messy, and disturbing. TV was not connected to antenna so you could not watch any TV broadcasts. Yes, you could use the internet services but many of them require your subscriptions. The sleeping corner (upper deck) was hot as the cold air from air-conditioner could not reach it (it's simple physics, cold air tends to go down rather than go up). They should have provided a fan at the upper deck for better circulation. I also found some bedsheets were left in the washing machine. By the way, no cloth hangers were provided.

Kristy's place was our first accommodation during our first trip to China. I have to say that after finding the correct building and entering the narrow staircase, you might be taken aback a little. The apartment is situated in an old historical building and during our stay, large construction works were underway.  Having entered the apartment, everything was as pictured in the listing (i.e. the apartment is fully renovated) , although accompanied with some dust from the construction works. Which is understandable. The bed was comfortable and clean. The same goes for the bathroom and towels. 

I would recommend Kristy's place if you are in search for a very authentic living experience in Shanghai. This place might not be for everyone, but we really grew into it over the course of our stay and are very happy we could experience living like a Shanghai local.

Kristy and her husband were very helpful and responded to our messaged quickly.

Excellent location - walking distance to the famous nanjing shopping strip, and close to the foreigner-friendly stores around west nanjing road. Loft is in the top floor of a old-style building (very nostalgic to me). Inside is very modern, but be prepared as the outside is very much not so (I.e. outdoor washing areas, smells..). Great if you want to experience a bit of old Shanghai in a central city location.

Kristy and her place are great. She was available when I asked for something and her clean, stylish apartment was in an excellent location. I have to go to Shanghai  about once a month and I hope to stay a Kristy's from now on since it is so reasonable and nice.

Spacy apartment with an afforested yard near Lujiazui CBD, and metro line 9 within walk distance connects it to the downtown. Simple and stylish furniture, nice design found in details: the stone table in the yard may inspire you for a backyard picnic, and the water hose offers some deeper interaction with this temporary accommodation. Feel at home, lay back in the couch and watch some movies with the projector. 
Equipment for the kitchen and bathroom meets basic demands. Dryer is not functioning very well but there is a fan heater in the bathroom, it works.

Apartment is very clean with a cute, private balcony attached to bedroom. Kitchen and bathroom facilities are new and updated. Only 1 flight of stairs walk up and less than 5min to subway. Definitely recommend!
Great location, plenty of space for two people and quick responses. Would definitely recommend!

Fiona's place had a fantastic location! The apartment was  a two minute walk from the line 2 and 11 which made the city feel very accessible. The main road was beautiful with plenty of nearby restaurants - both Chinese and Western. A great park for running or walking was only 10-15 minutes away. For foreigners who need to register with the police, the station is a five minute walk from the apartment and very easy to find. The space itself was a cosy two bedroom apartment with a small living area/kitchen and bathroom. It was a great home base for days spent exploring Shanghai. Fiona speaks great English and was always quick to respond to questions or comments!
Definitely good value for money. Highly recommended.
This home is in a great location. Very close to metro and lots of places to eat. Internet was was fast and reliable. The host is very nice and willing to help with any situation and give good advice.

Perfect location! Super close to subway stops and around 10-15 min walks to those famous restaurants/bars/pubs. The balcony is great too especially when you want a place to hangout and talk with your friends!

Yang's room in the French Concession is clean, convenient, and comfortable with all the essentials--perfect for short and long stays for business or pleasure. 

Yang was a super lovely and accommodating host. My flight was severely delayed and she kept in contact with me the entire time, and even greeted me (at 2am) at the entrance to her neighborhood and helped me carry my very heavy luggage up five flights of stairs. She is also an excellent cook and shared her home cooking with me!

I stayed with Yang during a work placement in Shanghai and it was perfect for  my needs. Great location, directly in the city center, easy to reach both business and leisure areas. Yang is a fantastic, very helpful host. She was very accommodating and helped me settle in and enjoy my time. I would definitely recommend for everyone to stay with Yang.

I love this place! Location-wise, it__ very convenient and right at the city center of Shanghai. Yang is super nice and communicative as well; she even helped me carry my two heavy bags upstairs. Highly recommend her place if you wanna find some budget accommodation in SH.

I stayed at Yang__ for 2 1/2 months and it was honestly one of the best Airbnb experiences I had! Yang__ apartment is so clean and she__ such a lovely host. The location is perfect for travellers who want to explore the city and close to many good restaurants and bars. I highly recommend others to stay here and will definitely stay with Yang again!

Yang is an extremely caring Host. If you wish so she leaves you alone and her space is very quiet. However, if you seek help or simply a conversation she is more than happy to engage with you. 

When I arrived she helped me carrying my luggage and helped me also to send a package by post. 

Since, the washing machine is in her room, she washes even the clothes for your. Moreover, she makes sure that there is always enough drinking water in your room. The room has many possibilities to store your luggage and is well adapted for long-term stays. 

Yang is a lovely Host ! I pretty much enjoyed staying at her place.

Yang is a very affable & hospitable host! The room is nicely prepared and the location is just wondrous. I will give it a 11/10 =) 

Also thanks so much for going through the trouble of couriering my travel adaptor to Hangzhou where I__ currently staying. Super appreciate that!

It was THE MOST BEAUTIFUL APARTMENT which i have ever seen in the real life!! If this place gonna be more central I would stay for whole trip and not picked only as plan B after the another host cancel my reservation. In each way...this plan B was surely way nicer & comfy than plan A

The apartment is great value for the price, and there are a couple of convenience stores and restaurants within walking distance. However, the bathroom had an issue with some ants and bugs on the floor.
The host canceled this reservation 4 days before arrival. This is an automated posting.

Yajun__ place is beautiful, cozy, convenient, comfortable and really cool. It__ centrally located for a great stay in one of the most fun neighborhoods in Shanghai. It__ close to major subways, right next to a bus stop and easy to catch a taxi. Yajun was super helpful and very hospitable. Really a great deal for Shanghai!

Yajun was a great host, she helped with our check-in as well as with some unrelated problems we had. The house has a modern touch to it and is in a very authentic neighborhood. Was great staying at this airbnb thank you Yajun!

Perfect little spot for our Shanghai adventure. Super close to the metro (if you are a foreigner don__ be scared of the metro it__ the easiest way to get around!). The place is in a little alley, and when we visited there was construction on the building... so LOTS of early morning noise. The stairs getting up were intensely steep and hard to navigate with big suitcases. But the place was adorable! Seriously so cute, felt like staying in what we call a __iny home_ in the US. Super clean. Host was amazingly helpful and gave great suggestions as well as directions in Chinese, which is a must if you are using a taxi. Everything was really clean. We loved it!
She's very helpful and had a great property. The place was spotless clean and had plentiful amenities

Great location less than 5 minute walk from Xintiandi station. Near several shopping centers, convenience stores, and a gym, Will's. Yajun recommended several places to visit including the gym I listed. The space was comfortable for two guests. Heads up - there is no shower curtain

Excellent Location in Shanghai!
A well equipped cozy department, we (our cat included) had a wonderful memory here.
Jin provided detail check in guidance, easy access for us.
Very charming space! We loved staying here.

The flat is a cozy corner in a very real part of Shanghai, with an excellent location and many bars/restaurants nearby. Yajun is very quick in responding and the self check-in is extremely convenient. The price is very reasonable considering the location and comparable peers!
The place was great! Great location.

Nice, clean, and very convenient place with lots of nice restaurants and bars around it

I greatly enjoyed my two day stay in Jun's apartment.  It is well located, just 4 or 5 minutes stroll from Xintiandi Metro station and therefore lots of choices for eating and easy access to the whole city.

Jun's instructions for finding the apartment were excellent since finding places in these small Chinese lane systems can be a challenge.

The apartment is great with a nice view of the street and by Jun's own admission the stairs up to it are a little steep and narrow but other than that it was great and the neighbours are very friendly.

Roxanne is a great host and happily answered all the questions I had. The home is small but tidy and nice and quiet compared to most places in China. It's a little tricky to find but Roxanne is a great help and gave some local tips as well. Metro station and restaurants just a short walk away, overall great place to stay - highly recommend.

Roxanne is a super nice host!! 
The house is very very beautiful and is indeed a place for people to relax, plus very convenient location(bars and restaurants within walking distance)
Definitely will come back again!

Roxanne could not have been a more wonderful host- she communicated very quickly, had a beautiful and clean space right in the heart of the best neighborhood in Shanghai, and checked in with me several times to ensure I was having a good stay. She is so thoughtful and lovely, and the bungalow is so charming and sweet. I would recommend this place to anyone in a heartbeat and hope to be back soon someday! Thank you Roxanne!
Great great location, close to metro, close to restaurants and shops, and Xujiahui Park.

What a gorgeous place to stay!  It is a small house in the middle of the French Concession part of Shanghai, and,  although small,  it has a small living room, a bedroom with a good double bed, a small kitchen and small bathroom. But all space is very efficiently used.  Roxanne is very communicative; she answers questions you may have fast and good (in proper English). A metro station is nearby, as are restaurants, bakery and other shops.  Roxanne had sent us a nice document with restaurants and other information. But let me not forget to mention the (again small) stunning place outside, where you can sit (quietly) in the shadow between all those nice plants and flowers.  A highly recommended place to stay.  One advice: although Roxanne's route description is excellent, it is good to have a maps app (with gps) on your mobile at hand. And remember: (Hidden by Airbnb) is blocked, unless you have a VPN or a Hong Kong based mobile card in your mobile phone (Website hidden by Airbnb) )

The Apartment is just wonderful! it is super stylish, you feel very safe, you have a nice terrace to sit outside, there is no noise from the streets at all, there are supermarkets, restaurants, shops and a metro station just a few minutes away. The host Roxanne is so kind and helps you out with everything! I highly recommend this apartment when staying in Shanghai!
Great place near city centre with lots of restaurants n food stalls.  Host responded quickly. Small place but cosy n clean.  Good for long or short stay.
Great apartment with the most beautiful little garden! Within walking distance to metro lines. Space is just nice for 2 people. Roxanne was great and friendly. Highly recommend!
Lovely place to stay! Quiet and great location!

Roxanne's place is stylish, clean and quiet. Good location in the French concession. Very near metro, shops, and restaurants. She was very helpful making sure we could find the apartment and answering all questions quickly. We would gladly stay again.
A super loving and thoughtful host. come with a few heaters to warm us up in freezing cold weather.  I love the garden too. its a good place to take photos.

Roxanne is a very responsive host and provided us with the walking routes and dinning suggestions nearby. We took a taxi from the Hongqiao Airport to her place and cost 49 RMB. Roxanne assisted us to direct the driver over the phone so he knew where to drop us off.  It__ very easy to explore the former French concession area from Roxanne__ place by foot. Her apartment is small but cozy, we got everything we needed for our stay. The highlights of her apartment are the skylight, floor heating system, washer/dryer and the little garden just outside the front door. I was very impressed how well she maintains her garden. The best moment in the morning is sitting in the hanging pod chair and enjoying the coffee in the garden.

This was the most pleasant stay me and my boyfriend have had! The apartment was clean and cozy with a lot of facilities. We can cook our own food! The location is convenient! We have a great host too.

The house on the outset was tidy and the area was decent too with convenient stores and Columbia Circle (a historical compound now used for restaurants and office space) and Disney is not so far.

It was amazing staying with Daisy!! She is super friendly and thoughtful. She allowed us to check in a bit earlier and to check out a bit later. 
Her space it__ amazing like no complains AT ALL!! Clean, that bed can fit 3 people, you have your own bathroom inside of the room, the view is stunning the room is big like perfect. 
You can also cook, wash and iron your clothes. Theirs towels and slippers as well but not toothbrush ( only toothpaste ) so prepare your own. 
Her compound it__ amazing, they have a indoor and outdoor pool, we only tried the indoor and it was 80ВҐ per person you need the swimsuit and the hat. 
From her place to Shanghai tower it takes 40 minutes by bus. The nearest subway station is Lancun Road ( line 4 ) and it takes 20 minutes walking to get to the apartment since I am a lazy human being I took a didi and it__ around 13/14ВҐ. 
To go to the clubs or bars takes 20/25minutes by didi/tГЎxi it costs around 30-45ВҐ if you take the subway it takes 1hour. 
Overall I would def recommend it to my friends and share the taxi bills, the space is nice and Daisy it__ amazing!
very clean and tidy. Nice hostess. Perfect experience.

My stay at Daisy's place was not at the right timing, which led to quite a bit of inconvenience for me.  I'll say it here so the next person can avoid the mistake I made. 
My trip took place on heavily rainy days in Shanghai. Now the place is in a big big gated community. The way that the ground was built doesn't seem to let rainwater flow down to the underground easily, which leads to big big deep pools of water. I was wearing only water-resistant shoes. I tried to call Didi, and Daisy told me Didi could get inside. However, every time I opened the app, it kept telling me to walk to the gate instead. Not to mention, it was very hard for me to get wifi inside the community. After 45 minutes passed with no way to get a Didi, I decided to just walk to the metro station, which is 20 minutes away. Now there are some bus lines outside the community, but none would take me to my destination. 
About the place: As I mentioned, it's inside a big gated community, so it's better to come by during day time. Although if you get lost, you can talk to the security guards. Daisy's communication is quick and fast too. The community is beautiful, green and clean. It's definitely a place for middle class Chinese. Her place is on the 18th floor, so the view is spectacular. I also find the fact that it's near a busy highway to be quite...poetic. Her place is clean, even for the kitchen, and is very quiet at night. There is this one dude who crashed on to sleep in the living room at night. I find it odd that I wasn't informed about him, but his presence didn't bother me much. I wish Daisy could have given a big bath towel for me though. All in all, however, it's a nice place. It's one of the first airbnb I stayed in Shanghai that is clean and beautiful inside and out - many of them are either only clean inside but the neighborhood is yuck!
Fast answer, good service, totally recommned
Daisy has been a great host with hospitality and friendliness, perfect experience with very clean room and nice apt, would recommend for all the friends around the world, thanks daisy!
safe and nice view in downtown

Other than that it's a place I would come back to again next time I visit.

Host gave me directions to another location that was posted on the Airbnb website, creepy guy walked inside while sleeping before Check out and stared at me and my girlfriend naked under blankets even after yelling to leave, elevator doesn__ work so expect to walk 8 floor up on grimy Chinese stairs, no dryer or hanger to dry clothes, overall sucks don__ get fooled by the __iew_ it isn__ worth it..

ж±__ place is in an ideal location, and has tremendous views. It it only a short 2 to 3 minute walk from the metro. My one piece of advice would be to make sure to check in before dark. The gate to the apartment entry is under security guard watch and they leave and lock the door once it gets dark.
All in all, a great place for the price.

In der unmittelbaren Umgebung gibt es ein schГ¶nes neues Einkaufszentrum mit tollen Restaurants (Thailaden/Erdgeschoss top). Mit dem Privat Taxi kommt man fГјr ca. 2 Euro bis zum Fernsehturm. Jiang was very great with communicating with us because me and my boyfriend arrived around 12am to the airbnb because our airbnb bike tour went longer than I expected. Jiang will give you a password to access her unit so make sure you have (Hidden by Airbnb) to communicate.

The home was very pleasant and spacious, beautiful city view, nice decor, 2 soft pillows, AC, clean bathroom, has a fridge, washer (in chinese), and fast wifi. 

Tip: If you do come late, the Bund will not be on at 12am so make sure you come before 10pm to take your night pictures from the airbnb because I didn't know it would be off at a certain time. Get a Chinese SIM card to get around by didi taxi (for cheap and can pay with cash!).

Amy was super helpful and her place was very clean! She went above and  beyond our needs to ensure we had a taxi to and from the airport (even for our late departure at 3am). She was so so helpful and for that I am incredibly thankful. She does not speak english, but I was able to converse with her just fine using (Hidden by Airbnb) translate. If you need to talk to someone, they usually typed in something on a translate service to let you know what is going on. Upon arrival, we had to wait because our room was being cleaned, but the host let us know via a translation on his phone. Everyone was so helpful on this property! This location is very close to the Chuansha Metro stop (which runs directly to the airport). It also has a Lawson Store on the corner of the building for buying simple necciesties such as snacks and water. This property functions kind of like a microtel (there is a very small front desk where we waited while I room was cleaned upon arrival). The host is really friendly, prompt in her reply and thoughtful gesture do matters. The place deco looks exactly the same as the photos shown. Is definitely a good location however be prepared to carry your luggage a few steps. Its a old building with no elevator so it's really for you to totally blend into experiencing the reality of the locals. We didn't expect much so is really still within our expectation. Easy to check in, just be sure your phone still have battery for you to switch on the lights if you are going out early or going back late as the corridor along the stairs ain't turn on. 
Subway is just near the building less than 2mins walk, and walkable distance to convenience stores, places to eat and shopping malls.
It can be really cold in the morning if you step out of the room to go to bathroom even though the windows are closed.

Very nice place to stay in Shanghai. Old, authentic building in Luwan district. I love this location. It is next to the metro station and you can reach many places by walk or bike.  Around the apartment, there are plenty of great restaurants. Chinese cuisine as well as some western style bakery or fast food. 
The apartment itself is rather small but enough for one or two people. AC and an additional heater make the place warm enough during cold winter days. 
Communication with Dara and her husband was perfect; they are very kind and support you during the whole time. Thanks again! 
All in all a great experience highly recommended!
You will find Tomi a great host.

Great tip-top communication with the owner with accurate check-in and out instructions. Condominium located in a good Metro accessible location within 3 mins of walking distance and 10-15mins of Metro travel to the Shanghai City. The condominium is newly renovated with all types of furniture, and all items of furniture (kitchen utilities, toilet utilities and beds) are all brand new. Thoroughly recommended for anyone who is looking for a good location, cosy and most importantly a clean place to stay in the City of Shanghai. 5 Stars given to this accommodation across all areas.

PANG HU and LAO YAN well deserved the superhost title. Both of them are easy going and helpful. The location is great. The room is stylish with great details and the view from the rooftop is stunning. Highly recommended.

Jing__ home is central, spacious, and comfortable. My friend and I got lost on our way to her home (Metro Tip: if you are coming from Pudong Airport there__ a metro upstairs that will take you directly to her house. You__l take Line 2 but it will not go all the way down to your stop, which is West Nanjing Road. You will need to get off and transfer to another L2 Train to finish your ride. It is marked underneath the stop names on the train which stops you can transfer at) Jing patiently waited for a couple hours as we made our way to her house without being able to contact her due to a lack of service/WiFi. Once we arrive her and her boyfriend met us at the door and checked us in and made sure we were comfortable. Her house is a quick 10-15 min walk from the train station and is surrounded by local markets, good food, and shops. We were at her house due to a long layover and Jing let us keep our bags inside her home as we killed time around the neighborhood before our flight. Jing ended up doing a tattoo on me and she is truly an impeccable artist and I highly recommend her if you are interested in trying it out. If I were to come to Shanghai again, I would definitely book this place.

The host is awesome, easy to communicate. The room looks exactly like in the pictures, cute, stylish, and clean. Overall it's a lovely place to stay, with only one catch -- the stairs going up are narrow and steep, not suitcase friendly.

Jin__ place exceeded our expectation on its location and overall experience. It enriched our stay in shanghai greatly, and we were very happy for this choice! Thank you! Hope to stay again next time. All best wishes,

Jing's place is in a very central location, easy to access from the metro. Place is clean and well kept. I did not get to meet Jing, but she was quick to my responses, even though there was a language barrier she did connect me with her English speaking friend to answer my questions. The address is incorrect on Airbnb, I would check in with Jing on the instructions to get to her place. Being a solo traveller, I did feel a bit uncomfortable going to a location that was different from what was listed. But Jing made me feel safe and provided all the instructions to find her home which was easy to understand.
Very good location to city centre, friendly host!

Jing's place was amazing. The room and location are perfect.  It was easy to use the subway. The location is very close to the city and downtown. Train fares are cheap. We could go everywhere we want. If I had said, we couldn't find her house. It is difficult to find her house for foreigners. However, Jing helped us a lot. She is very sweet. The room is better than I expected. We used the terrace at night. You need careful to go up and downstairs. The stairs are narrow and steep. I enjoyed my stay in Shanghai with her house. I recommend staying at her house.

Great location and very quick communication with host.

Candice and her husband were excellent hosts. They were able to clearly get us to their place where everything was neat and orderly. The air conditioning was cold and the Wifi was quick so we were pleased. Candice's husband also took us to the airport in the morning which was a great relief. I highly recommend!
Candice__ place was really clean and had all the necessary amenities. Thanks for the hospitality!
Rest assured she__ got you. I__ rather take her pick up and drop off services than a taxi.

Candice__ place was very clean, comfortable, and well-appointed. My group of four had plenty of room during our long layover in Shanghai, and the location was very convenient to the airport. Candice and her father went above and beyond to ensure that our stay was comfortable, even going so far as to offer airport pickup and drop off service, as well as an extra ride to the Maglev station. Candice was very responsive to messages and very easy to communicate with. Thank you, Candice and family, for your hospitality.
Clean sheets, fast internet, and hot shower. I had all I needed for travel. Good response in guiding me to the right location.

Candice helped us every step of the way! She was very helpful and her father waited 3 hours for us to get through customs at the airport. We almost forgot our phone in the car and they drove back to return it. Our only issue was being unable to find any food near by that spoke English.
nice and I would come again

The space was as described. the beds were very hard which is comfortable if you like sleeping on a hard bed. The ride to and from the airport was a great touch however, and her father was helpful beyond words. overall a nice stay
The outside of the accommodation is too dark

I missed the message from the hostess so that we had a really hard time figuring out how to get to the house but everything worked out really well after we get there. The hostess and her family were really nice and kind. We enjoyed our stay at Candice__. Thank you.

Great place to stay!! Her father's pick up and drop off service is so convenient and he's super nice! Candice's English is also really good and she is very responsive! Highly recommend! It is a bit far from the main city of Shanghai but that's okay!

For those looking for a place for quick transfer to airport..this is the right place! We had an early morning flight from Pudong, and Candice's pick up and drop off service make it even easier for us. Her father was so nice to us. He drove us from subway, to and from disneyland and to the airport. Candice was so quick to response to my message. Overall, everything was good!

Had a great stay at Candice's place. It is not too far from the airport but quite far from the city center. The local shops are a treat if you want to experience how the locals live. There are fresh markets as well as a lot of food places around. Would highly recommend if you are looking for a place to stay close to the airport for the night without having to spend much and experience some local culture.

Candice__ home was everything we needed and more. First off, it was an amazing value and it is super close to the airport. My husband and I were traveling with our our two dogs and Candice was so accommodating and made us and our pups feel right at home. The neighborhood is very cute, and you are able to find a Walmart and many places to eat within 1.6 miles of her home, I recommend using a didi as this is a very cheap and convenient option for local travel. Her home was exceptionally clean and the beds were much more comfortable than the typical chinese bed (I have lived in China for a year and my bed was much harder). We truly enjoyed everything about our stay and highly recommend Candice__ home. And as an added bonus the dogs that belonged to other members of the neighborhood were super cute and friendly to our dogs as well! Thank you for such an amazing transition into our new life back in America!
Candice__ place was very aesthetically pretty and clean. Candice always replies very quickly! Her father picked us up from the airport and dropped us off which was super helpful.
We enjoyed our stay here. Amazing hospitality and nearby to the airport.

Candice is the best Airbnb host I have ever had. The space was a bit different than I was expecting (not in the nicest area and a bit smaller than described as a __ouse_) BUT I only paid $30 for it and it was WELL worth the money and a great place to crash for the night. Candace is amazingly responsive and even offered ride service from and to the airport for very cheap, which was so helpful.
Great place if you need to stay close to the airport. Candice is very helpful and super quick in responding to any questions! Thanks!
Great location! Small loft, but great for 1-2 people.

Positive points:
- great location in the heart of Shanghai, in a charming market.
- the room is very well arranged and impeccably clean.
- the host is reactive enough.
- excellent value for money compared to many other similar places for rent.

Negative point:
- the room is in an old Shanghai-style house, so there is no soundproofing whatsoever. The heavy steps and conversations of neighbours left, right and above can be heard clearly. Recommend this airbnb to those wanna stay in Shanghai x modern style apartment

This was a very stylish apartment is a convenient part of the city. We were able to walk (within 10-30minutes) to many of the bars and restaurants we wanted to check out -and the others were just a short taxi/subway ride away. Being directly opposite a movie theater was a nice bonus. The apartment is in an older complex (typical in that part of Shanghai) which made finding the place a bit tricky at night in the rain. If you are arriving after dark it would be good to have a flashlight with you! The bathroom is a bit claustrophobic but there was plenty of hot water. Shanghai is very humid (even in the winter so the bathroom floor was wet most of the time -be sure to make use of those shower shoes. The balcony was great and I bet it is super awesome in the warmer months. Kitchen supplies were minimal so if you are planning to cook you might have to get inventive or drop into the giant supermarket across the street.
Great stay and very much recommended.

This place is a great example on the importance of interior design. It's nestled in the middle of a low cost flat with surroundings that are quite "salt-of-the-earth". We had a sense of dread walking up and down the flats trying to find the property. But it felt like entering into another world when we finally found it! Which was a pleasant surprise.

It was at first a bit difficult to find the room and I wasn't sure if I was in the right place because of the entrance, which is a bit hidden in the courtyard of a residential building. But as I found the room I was impressed by the beauty of its interiors and the pleasant and cosy atmosphere. You could instantly tell that CloГ© has taste a hand for interior design. Furthermore, CloГ© helped me every time I was in need of something. I stayed in Shanghai for three weeks and as I do not speak Mandarin, I had a lot of questions regarding food and Chinese culture. CloГ© was very helpful and always nice. I especially enjoyed her recommendations for restaurants. She is an expert for food from different Chinese provinces and so my trip to Shanghai turned out to be also a round trip through Chinese cuisine. Thanks to that and to the beautiful and ideally situated apartment near the metro, I had a wonderful stay there and hope to come back soon.

Fantastic location. In a 1930 heritage building in the heart of French quarter. Cool cheap restaurants around ( i recommend Tai Fan across the road). Quite comfortable and heater/ac works well. Wifi works well. TV. The bed is bigger than expected., although a bit hard for my old back, but that's a matter of taste.. There s little sofa. The room is bigger than expected. There are enough place for storing big suitcase and hangers and shelves for clothes and also a brand new fridge and a microwave. Unbeatable for the price. And I shall repeat: the location is amazing and rather quite for an old house!

A simple room for one person, and the surroundings for life function is complete.

The Room and its attached bathroom are on the third floor of an antique building which is a part of the Former French Concession that reflects its amazing location. In addition to that there are plenty of shops and convenient stores right outside the neighborhood. 
The place was simple yet pleasant and warm. The range of amenities is convenient. Especially, the heater, AC and the bathroom bulb heater which all together made a huge difference in the current cold weather in the middle of winter. In fact, living in such antique room confers the resident an exceptional experience of living in a different era, the wooden staircase is designed to be helical  and narrow which may troublesome anyone with a large luggage, moreover the wooden staircase creates not easily to  be ignored noise which woke us up frequently early in the morning or in the middle of the night each time a neighbor guest climbing down/up the stairs. Furthermore, as a resultant of the building old-fashion structure which stacks rooms close to each other, residents can literally hear each other while performing their daily home-chores such as cleaning dishes in their kitchen, it can be annoying especially in the early mornings. At the end, I must mention the owner kindness and communicativeness, I experienced that because I usually add the owners on (Hidden by Airbnb) directly before checking-in to smoothen the communication between us, he responded as soon as I sent him the invitation request and he sent me all the relative details for the location, in addition to the passwords of 3 different wifi networks which their speeds varies frequently during the day. 
Over all, good value for money.

Everything worked perfectly, including reliable high speed wifi. The view overlooking Xujiahi park is amazing. Laurent was a great host, responsive and effective.
This apartment was perfect for our stay! Clean, comfortable beds, great shower, and amazing view. Laurent and his team were always quick to respond and made the stay super easy.
good location, very nice decoration and the master bedroom is very nice
Good place to stay. Great location and nicely appointed.

Laurent is a great host and was very helpful in organising a driver to and from the airport but if your travelling with less luggage then the train/metro is easy to navigate.
Laurent__ place is exactly like advertised but the addition of an instructional manual would__e helped greatly.
shopping mall and the subway station is quite close from the apt :)) and the view inside is super amazing!!!

We definitely recommend Laurent__ place!

One thing to note is the life sized terra-cotta worrier statue standing outside the rooms, to some it is a nice art piece but to some it can be pretty scary.

Great location, close to the metro. The apartment is tastefully decorated and full of character. Laurent showed great commitment to being a helpful host in an extraordinary time in China; he provided helpful advise and excellent communication. I'd recommend this apartment to anyone who wants to be close to the centre of Shanghai but in a more relaxed community.

Meiling__ place is in a very good location in the Former French concession. It is easily accessible by Metro via Changshu Road station, probably a 6-8 minute walk. There are also buses nearby. As for the neighborhood, it could not be any better. There are lots of local and foreign restaurants and bars nearby.

It is on the second floor of an old apartment building so you will have to walk up one flight of stairs.

The apartment is cozy and compact and has pretty much everything you need. The only issue is the bathroom sometimes had a smell, typical of apartments in the area but hopefully, it can be treated/rectified soon. 

Although we had to rely on translation apps, Meiling was a great host overall, very responsive and looked after us during our stay at her place.
The Appartement is in a nice area and is quite spacious. The host is nice but doesn't speak any english.

I stayed here for two nights over the weekend and couldn't be happier.  The apartment is clean and thoughtfully put together.  Plus, the location is perfect. The host was amazing, answering any question or offering help when needed immediately.  She does not speak English, but that was easily rectified with (Hidden by Airbnb) and translation ;). 

Great apartment, amazing location and fantastic host.  Book this place, you will love it.
an enjoyable stay in a good part of the city. slightly surprised to find it was in a love hotel, but not an issue. host very good at answering questions, good value. great projector for films

Exactly as per the photos. Bigger space than most other apartments for this price. All necessary amenities. Very pleasant view from balcony. Comfortable bed. Very nice and responsive host. Good location. Mall and supermarkets around. Bus and metro nearby. Very good stay. :)

We had to put towel down so catch the water. Except for that, it was a great place

Thanks so much for being a good host. The location is perfect just walking distance to the nanjing east road and subway is very very nearby at the hongyi plaza. Easy for us who are travelling with kids. But was quite shock when we arrived because of the environment outside the house. However, when you enter the house, it is exactly the same as what is being describe in the picture. Lao has been very helpful since we are at Malaysia before we checked in. He gave few tips about shanghai and was very fast in responding. He even prepared some umbrellas for us. That was very thoughtful of him, knowing that shanghai was raining during our stay. Overall, i am satisfied with the stay.
At a great location, with a nice host, you can experience how local people live there, and super easy to access to restaurants and the Bund. Totally worth the value.

The apartment location is perfect, 5 minutes from the Bund. The apartment itself is very well designed, shiny and pretty clean and with 3 double beds. Only thing in the apartment is that the toilet had some bad odor at moments from the pipes so better close the door when not using. Also the air con had a little leak so some water going down. Also the building and floor entrance is a common area for locals to cook, wash, toilet etc. Nothing wrong in itself but this could be informed as a bit shocking when arriving. All in all very good value for this apartment in the heart of the city and very cosy.

Great stay! Didn't expect much due to the location being in an old area, but its definitely much better than seen outside, pictures provided are very accurate. Air con broke down on the second night, but fixed within 12 hours while we were out and never had problems anymore, overall 10/10

Tourist from Malaysia...
Owner is quite responsive and friendly even in the midnight around 2am. 3 beds (2 Queen 1 sofa bed) basically can fit 5ppl of us. Besides, spaceful room and great location. Just walk some few mins and you will see NanJing walk street together with MRT station.

Few things to note.
1. I had checked in at the midnight at 230am. Before walk into owner's  house. The area was dark and creepy without street light, even phone torch was not helpful at all. Not recommended for girls accommodation.
2. Lift to owner's home.
Lift will be off around 11pm and we need to climb stairs to 3rd floor. According to owner, lift is still new and this was their area rules. Luckily, lift was still functioned on the first day in the midnight with the heavy luggages we are holding.

Overall, quite impressive that big difference compared to internal environment (owner house) and external environment (before entering the house). Design and cozy living. Thanks for the wonderful place for living!
The host was quick in responding and the house is exactly like the picture showed. Value for money.
Perfect location. Close to all POIs. The apartment is clean with all necessary facilities. Quick response from the owner.
Location is great. Walking distance to a lot of tourist places

The place is in good location. Near the Bundt (left) and Nanjing pedestrian street(right) and subway  aline 2/10 (exit 3/right) from the main gate. The building is old but the house is nice and neat.The host replies fast.
Great location and very fast response from the host, it was perfect

The stay is at the 3rd floor, there is an elevator to 3rd floor. Host is very responsive & friendly. Host is always helpful. Location is superb, 2 mins walk to Nanjing east road metro station. The building is a bit old but the room provided is in good condition & clean. The room is well ventilated. U can refer to host picture for the room, is almost the same.

The location of this apartment is great, only a couple of minutes from the Bund, despite the building is a bit old and dark, the apartment is very clean and well decorated, it feels you are in 2 different places (outside and inside) We were 5 people and the space was good enough for all of us.  
The only thing we didn__ like it was the conditioner air, it was very cold in Shanghai and we felt the aircon wasn__ strong enough to heat the whole apartment but we could handle it, further the apartment has nice blankets and it we enjoyed the time there.  Thanks to the host for the help and understanding about my checkin time.

Location is a gem right in the middle of Shanghai central next to Nanjing Road, totally value for the price!   Host is really fast in responding to message and help in anyway.  Thank you again in hosting our family for a week at your place :)

Just walking distance to central shopping malls and popular sightseeings. The huge window provides u with sunshine and perfect view!

The homestay is very clean and comfortable, with no complicated layouts and everything is just right. Indoor heating feels especially warm in such winters. The location of the house is very good. It is located on West Nanjing Road. There is Metro Line 2 next to it. It is convenient to go drinking and shopping. Thanks for the care of the landlord. I will stay here next time in Shanghai.

Excellent location with easy access to many historical sites and good local food, shopping areas. The building was built in 1930s with lots of history. I really enjoyed live here for 3 days and have a chance to try the local life and recall the history happened here in the pasty 80 years while so many changes happened. 
The room is well designed and carefully cleaned. The neighbor is very friendly which is very good as I did met some bad neighbors when stay in the downtown  BNB in Paris and San Francisco. 
What make us very happy is that it is very warm in the room.  Joyce provided 3 air conditions to keep it warm. It used to be very cold in the room in southern Chinese cities. I kept ask Joyce about the room temperatures before check in. She make her promise and it is really warm.
Although I did not have the chance to meet Joyce, I could fell her hospitality as she always reply very soon. Hope to be able to come back again and stay in this lovely room.

This is a very quiet and cozy living space , with comfortable and soft bed.  Great  location,friendly host.  I would recommend it to friends.

It was a very good experience staying in Ricky__ Apt.  His apt is in an old style SH Shikumen House with European style inner decoration. Very nice!
I had a private room with a private washroom even if I stayed with Ricky. He gave me lots of personal space but also with quick response when I had some questions. 
The place is in the center of SH and old French concession area. 10 mins walk to Line 13 and 15 mins walk to Line 1/12/10. Very convenient!
The house is located in the centre. There are many good bars near the residence. Btw Ricky is very warm-hearted. I quite enjoy my stay here.
Very nice location, there are a lot of shop, bar and bistro around the house. The living room is comfortable.

Ricky__ apartment is located in the quiet but convenient part of Shanghai. The room is enough big for single to live in. Great location! Nice neighborhood of FFC area! Ricky is very nice and helpful host. Definitely recommend to anyone who want to explore Shanghai central area.
Ricky is kind and gentle, had a good night in this sweet house . Wlc to BJ, Hope to see u soon)
Stayed an extra night. Nice place.
Stylish place, located in a great neighborhood, cool host. Everything was great.

Exceptional host and location in the beautiful French Concession.
Ricky's affable demeanor, local knowledge, and warm and welcoming space really helped me settle in, relax, and enjoy my time in Shanghai.
Thank you Ricky, that is really clearly about the direction you sent the message. Like the picture in the room. Nice bathroom in the old house.

The location of this place is very good. There are convenience stores and delicious restaurants near the subway station. The host was very kind and knew a lot of information about Shanghai. While I was in Shanghai, I had fun and good memories.

Nice and friendly place to stay!

I recommend Ricky__ place to Young folks who want to experience modern mixes with old Shanghai and rich night life.

1. Great location, probably the best neighborhood in Shanghai. Top bars like Speck Low are right outside. Easy to access metro and buses if you take public transportation. Plenty of restaurants are available. 

2. The room is in an old Shanghai residential building. Not as fancy as the modern condos, but is a type of place that old shanghaiers live before and now. You can see the locals dry their blankets out from the windows when is sunny. Lol. The room is not very big but it got bed, closet and private bathroom. What__ else do you need?

3. Ricky is a very welcoming and friendly. He send me the map and direction from metro train station to his place and introduced us the neighborhood with some good places to go. He responds very quickly as well.
This is a clean and comfortable room. Its location is perfect, with the atmosphere of traditional Shanghai life in the community. Ricky is a very nice guy. Thanks!
Great location, walking distance to cafes & restaurants. A close experience to Shanghai__ neighbourhoods.
Very warm and neat place, thanks for having me to stay in your place, I had a wonderful vacation in Shanghai.

You will enjoy a good time if you plan to rent Ricky's apartment. He will give you a warm welcome, at the same time keep a comfortable distance with you during your stay. But don't worry you could always ask him if you need any help. 

You could share nearly all the space and appliances in the apartment, for me I really like his big cozy living room with such a high ceiling height.
